text: Andrea Ramírez Fregoso (born 25 September 1999) is a Mexican professional racing cyclist, who currently rides for UCI Women's Continental Team . On 28 June 2019 she won the Mexican women's time trials, and two days later came second at the national road race championships. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Mexican female cyclists Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
